programme.desc: Hal Gahm returns to the amazing Sproul Ranch of west Texas for an up-close and personal aoudad experience.(n)

programme.title: Elk Camp
programme.desc: Steve Chappell guides Bob Saban who drew a tag for the Muzzleloader Elk hunt in Arizona's legendary Unit 9.(n)

programme.title: Wildlifers
programme.desc: Stephanie Braman is back in New Mexico with her son Race on his first New Mexico bear hunt.(n)

programme.title: Petersen's Hunting Adventures
programme.desc: Kevin Steele treks to the cedar breaks and coulees of north-central Nebraska for a shot at a big prairie whitetail.(n)

programme.title: Extreme Outer Limits TV
programme.desc: A look back at Bob Beck's hunts in 2015 and 2016 where he hunts during the late season and hopes to find a giant Oregon bull.(n)

programme.title: Whitetail Properties
programme.desc: Both Aaron Milliken and Justin Mason have begun development on their new properties. Each are located within the infamous golden triangle. Each farm has unique traits that stand out as great wildlife habitats.(n)

programme.title: Huntin' the Backwoods
programme.desc: Karl and Paul return to Africa to hunt plains game animals at Koringkoppie Safaris. This is Karl's sixth trip to Africa, but Paul has some catching up to do.(n)

programme.title: North American Whitetail Television
programme.desc: Mike Clerkin heads to the legendary Buffalo County, Wisc. in search of early-season whitetail action and Dr. Deer identifies must-have equipment for small land managers.(n)

programme.title: Outback Outdoors
programme.desc: Part 1. Trevon and Dave return to western Nebraska to share some camaraderie, laughs and to match their spot-and-stalk skills against the deer of the Sandhills.(n)

programme.title: Greg McHale's Wild Yukon
programme.desc: Greg travels by dogsled into wood bison country. The Yukon's late winter offers good travel conditions with plenty of snow and comfortable temperatures, at least until the frozen rivers begin to wake.(n)

programme.title: Under Wild Skies
programme.desc: Tony heads to the hill town of Cortona, Italy for wingshooting and great cuisine and wine. He stays at Il Falconeire, a Relais and Chateau in the shadow of Cortona where he hunts, eats and drinks the local wine.(n)

programme.title: Trijicon's World of Sports Afield
programme.desc: Jason Hornady and Neil Davies need membership into the Lucky Hunters Hall Of Fame for drawing a coveted buddy tag for bull elk in northwest Nebraska.(n)

programme.title: The Fierce Life
programme.sub-title: Send It... Fierce Long Range Shooting School
programme.desc: Experience the annual Fierce Long Range Shooting School.(n)

programme.title: RNT-V
programme.desc: The RNT Goose Krewe is getting settled in their home away from home as the migration comes to full swing.(n)

programme.title: Avian-X TV
programme.desc: Join Fred Zink as he hunts divers in Canada alongside his father and world champion carvers, Dick Rhode and Rick Johannsen.(n)

programme.title: Bill Dance Saltwater
programme.desc: Part 1. Anchor fishing in a swift, strong current, Bill Dance and Captain Steve Crowder redfish the St. Johns River.(n)

programme.title: Sweetwater
programme.desc: Kayaks allow anglers to target multiple species all across the country. Miles and Joey do just that in their Old Town Predators.(n)

programme.title: Respect the Game TV
programme.desc: Paul and Ty Biggs have struggles and success in their home state of Oklahoma. Whitetail is in their blood.(n)

programme.title: Razor Dobbs Alive
programme.sub-title: Razor Dobbs Goes UTV Terracross Racing
programme.desc: Razor Dobbs races the Terracross UTV championships.(n)

programme.title: Out-There TV
programme.desc: Each spring, Corey Brossman finds himself busy as a beaver. From shed hunting to turkey hunting and everything in between. Corey chases gar in Kansas with his AMS bowfishing gear.(n)

programme.title: Hornady's Dark & Dangerous *
programme.desc: Meghan Hornady, along with hunters Clay Eifling and Zackary Core, will write new chapters into their own safari journal of memories. We're in Zimbabwe and Tanzania for dangerous game hunting at it's best.(n)

programme.title: Extreme Outer Limits TV
programme.desc: A look back at Bob Beck's hunts in 2015 and 2016 where he hunts during the late season and hopes to find a giant Oregon bull.(n)

programme.title: Backcountry Hunters TV
programme.desc: Hal Gahm returns to the amazing Sproul Ranch of west Texas for an up-close and personal aoudad experience.(n)

programme.title: Handguns And Defensive Weapons
programme.desc: Jim and Scott team up with FTW's Doug Dog Prichard to tackle long-range target shooting with bolt actions and semi-automatics. Scott explains how the circle drill can improve handgun proficiency. Also: Rich explains the concept of targeting.(n)

programme.title: Gallery of Guns
programme.sub-title: Bolt Action, Rimfire, AR & Lever Action
programme.desc: Firearm reviews from Remington, Rossi, SIG SAUER and Henry will be on the range. Guns & Ammo editor Eric Poole will also give a shooting tip on the very popular Ruger 10/22.(n)

programme.title: All Things Hunting - ATH
programme.desc: Part 2. The crew is hunting African plains game with Majeje Africa Safaris. The action is fast and adrenaline-filled as they spot-and-stalk hunt for kudu, nyala, gemsbuck, and more.(n)

programme.title: Red Rising
programme.desc: Jason Bowers takes his friend Lindsey out hunting in Virginia. Jason has her on a buck in Virginia, however, the result ends differently than expected.(n)

programme.title: Big Deer TV
programme.desc: Mike sits and shivers for 50 hours in the frozen Canadian timber.(n)

programme.title: Bowhunter TV
programme.desc: Bowhunter Magazine Editor Curt Wells lives his life-long dream of taking all five species of North American deer. In "Moment of Truth," Curt shares can't-miss advice on binoculars.(n)

programme.title: Whitetail Fix *
programme.desc: Matt arrives at the Weldon compound after driving all night, just in time to climb a stand and arrow a nice buck on the first evening.(n)

programme.title: Easton Bowhunting TV
programme.desc: We use different tactics, including waterholes and horses, to get in bow range of pronghorn antelope.(n)

programme.desc: Steve and his brother head to the Mills Creek region in Alaska's Kenai Peninsula.(n)
